<!DOCTYPE recipe [<!ELEMENT recipe ((title?,details?,ingredients, instructions?,cuisine) | (title?,cuisine,details?,ingredients, instructions?))><!ELEMENT title (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT cuisine (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT ingredients (ingredient*)><!ELEMENT ingredient (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT instructions (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT details (#PCDATA)><!ATTLIST ingredient amount CDATA #REQUIRED>]>
<recipe>
<title>
Roasted Garlic Guacamole
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 15 minutes
COOK TIME: 30 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 45 minutes
COURSE: Condiment
CUISINE: Mexican
KEYWORD: avocado
SERVINGS: 6 servings
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="15.0">Garlic</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 tsp ">Olive Oil</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0">Avocado</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 tsp ">Juice</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 F.
Lay a piece of aluminum foil flat.
Put garlic cloves in a single layer on foil, and drizzle with olive oil.
Wrap up foil to form a packet.
Bake for about 30-40 minutes, or until garlic is golden brown and soft.
Let cool.
Add avocados to a bowl.
Drizzle with lime juice, and then mash to desired consistency.
Stir in pico de gallo, and sprinkle with salt.
</instructions>
<cuisine>Mexican</cuisine></recipe>